The President of the United States, Barack Obama, spoke with Prime Minister David Cameron of the United Kingdom about the ongoing situation in Ukraine. Both leaders expressed their serious concern over Russia's violation of Ukrainian sovereignty and territorial integrity. They agreed that the current circumstances are unacceptable and discussed the negative consequences Russia is facing, such as reduced investor confidence. The leaders also welcomed the military observer mission by the Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe, which was requested by the Ukrainian government. They talked about providing support to stabilize Ukraine's economy and prepare for upcoming elections in May. They agreed to maintain close contact in the coming days.